<subsection xml:id="formulas-for-chapter-2" class="unnumbered">
	<title>Formulas for Chapter 2</title>

	<p>
		<term>Percent Change Formula:</term> If a quantity increases by a percentage corresponding to growth rate <m>r</m>, then the growth factor is <me>\displaystyle g=1+r</me>
	</p>

	<p>
		<term>Compound Interest Formula:</term> <m>\displaystyle a = p \left( 1 + \frac{r}{12}\right) ^{12y}</m>
	</p>

	<p>
		<term>Equivalent APR Formula:</term> <m>\displaystyle \text{APR} = \left(1+\frac{r}{12}\right)^{12}-1</m>
	</p>

	<p>
		<term>Future Value Annuity Formula:</term> <m>\displaystyle a = p \ast \frac{\left( 1 + \frac{r}{12}\right) ^{12y}-1}{\frac{r}{12}}</m>
	</p>

	<p>
		<term>Loan Payment Formula:</term> <m>\displaystyle p = \frac{a  \ast \frac{r}{12}}{1-\left( 1 + \frac{r}{12}\right) ^{-12y}}</m>
	</p>

	<p>
		where
	</p>

	<tabular>
		<row class="odd">
		<cell halign="left"><m>a</m> = account balance or loan amount ($)</cell>
	</row>
		<row class="even">
		<cell halign="left"><m>p</m> = initial deposit (principal), regular deposit, or regular payment ($)</cell>
	</row>
		<row class="odd">
		<cell halign="left"><m>y</m> = time invested (years)</cell>
	</row>
		<row class="even">
		<cell halign="left"><m>r</m> = interest rate compounded monthly (as a decimal)</cell>
	</row>
	</tabular>
</subsection>
